data.label: Ada
data.description: A health-focused chatbot designed to assess symptoms and provide medical guidance, not diagnoses.

data.label: characterAI
data.description: A role-play–focused platform where you chat with fictional or custom characters, emphasizing personality, creativity, and storytelling.

data.label: ChatGPT
data.description: An open-domain chatbot for conversation, writing, coding, learning, and creative tasks

data.label: Deepseek
data.description: An open-domain chatbot geared toward technical reasoning, coding, and analytical tasks, often compared to research-focused assistants.

data.label: Gemini
data.description: Google’s AI assistant, designed for productivity, search-connected tasks, multimodal input (text/images), and real-time information.

data.label: Paradot
data.description: A social companion chatbot focused on emotional bonding, long-term memory, and personalized conversation.

data.label: Replika
data.description: A social companion chatbot aimed at emotional support, friendship, and role-play, with a strong emphasis on mental well-being.

data.label: Rocky
data.description: A mental-health and coaching chatbot focused on resilience, mindset, and goal clarity.

data.label: SeniorTalk
data.description: A social companion chatbot designed for older adults, emphasizing companionship, simplicity, and daily conversation.

data.label: Supertutor
data.description: An educational chatbot focused on tutoring, explaining concepts, and helping students learn or practice academic subjects.

data.label: Talkpal
data.description: An educational chatbot for language learning that helps users practice speaking, grammar, and vocabulary through conversation.

data.label: Wysa
data.description: A mental-health chatbot offering Cognitive Behavioral Therapy-based techniques, mood tracking, and emotional support.

data.label: Image Chat Message
data.description: A message containing or only consisting of an image.

data.label: Video Chat Message
data.description: A message containing or only consisting of a video.

data.label: GIF Chat Message
data.description: A message containing or only consisting of a GIF.

data.label: Sticker Chat Message
data.description: A message containing or only consisting of a Sticker.

data.label: Voice Chat Message
data.description: A voice-based message transferred via call, voice-to-text, or voice message.

data.label: Web Preview Chat Message
data.description: A preview on web content from other providers or the chatbot homepage itself.

data.label: Emoji Chat Message
data.description: A message containing or only consisting of an emoji or emoticon.

data.label: Carousel Chat Message
data.description: A set of similar items presented in a horizontal list.

data.label: Accordion
data.description: Used to hide information to save space, either shortening long messages or summarizing multiple results. Some chatbots also include a similar option to show more Quick Reply for the users.

data.label: Message Action
data.description: Emojis or menus beside or under a chat to act on the chatbot’s message, like copying, regenerating, playing, flagging or sharing the message.

data.label: Processing Indicator
data.description: A visual representation of the waiting time for the reply of the chatbot.

data.label: Persistent Menu
data.description: A constant menu in the chat window for important information or settings.

data.label: Functionality Introduction
data.description: Introducing the main functionalities or providing a tutorial in the first chat messages.

data.label: Quick Start Button
data.description: A set of action buttons to start a conversation that is focused on specific topics or actions, like making a plan or creating an image.

data.label: Conversation Recovery
data.description: Avoiding conversation breakdowns by providing possible actions or commands.

data.label: Dialog Reload
data.description: Avoiding conversation breakdowns by providing possible actions or commands.

data.label: Information Stamp
data.description: Inclusion of contextual information such as the time, date, and sender associated with chat messages, displayed above or below the message.

data.label: Extended Input
data.description: A possibility to upload extra information in form of documents or media. It can also be a request for specific actions of chatbot, like generating an image or a story.

data.label: Input Adjustment
data.description: A request for how the chatbot should generate answers, e.g. answering "thinking" mode versus giving a fast response.

data.label: Interactive Canvas
data.description: A shared graphical or text-based workspace for collaboration, e.g. for writing code or drawing together with the chatbot.

data.label: Message Completion
data.description: Suggestions for completion of the chat message when typing a request. This feature is also found in search engines.

data.label: Text Chat Message
data.description: Displaying outputs from chatbot and user, most often as speech bubbles.

data.label: Quick Reply
data.description: A set of actions or functionalities under a chat message in the form of buttons.

data.label: Call-on Menu
data.description: A dynamic representation of consistent information which was requested by the user.

data.label: Message Reaction
data.description: Emojis beside or under a chat message to provide feedback on the answer of the chatbot.

data.label: Help System
data.description: Offering assistance for users, either on request or proactively by the chatbot.

data.label: System Information
data.description: Information provided outside the conversation, such as data protection notices in form of pop-ups banners or like “news tickers” above or underneath the respective footer or header of the chatbot.

data.label: Avatar
data.description: A digital representation of a human user that facilitates interaction with other users, entities, or the environment.
